Vice President Mike Pence welcomed members of the Philanthropy Roundtable to the White House, thanking them for their contributions to advancing liberty, opportunity, and personal responsibility. Pence discussed the importance of charitable giving and its connection to economic growth. He highlighted the administration's efforts to roll back regulations and create jobs, as well as their commitment to repeal and replace Obamacare. Pence expressed support for the Senate healthcare bill, stating that it would restore freedom and affordability to American healthcare. He urged members of the Senate to pass the bill and send it to President Trump's desk. Pence also emphasized the importance of the charitable deduction and called for an increase in charitable giving. The Vice President expressed his optimism about the Senate bill and stated that the administration would work hard to ensure its passage.